						<summary>

						<p>This registers the gift of a silver pot weighing 294 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> for the <hi rend="italic">abhishēka</hi> (bath) of the god by a queen (Nambirāṭṭiyār) whose name is not clear. It might perhaps be Nak[kaṉ Aru]moḻi Prati[mādeviyār] (See No. 349 below). Tiruviśalūr is here stated to have formed part of Vēmbaṟṟūr <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śōḻamārttāṇḍa-chaturvēdi maṅgalam, a <hi rend="italic">dēvadāna-brahmadēya</hi> situated in Maṇṇi-nāḍu a subdivision of Rājēndrasimha-vaḷanāḍu to the north of the river.</p>						

						</summary>
